# Commit and push after changes

When you **finish** a task that changes tracked files in this repo (code, content, styles, generated `assets/css/main.css`, etc.):

1. Run `git status` in the repo you edited.
2. If there are changes worth keeping, **`git add`** the relevant paths, **`git commit`** with a short, accurate message, and **`git push`** to **`origin`** on the current branch.

**Do not** end the session with only local edits when the user expected delivery—push unless they explicitly asked for “no commit”, “plan only”, or “don’t push yet”.

**Skip** committing when: there is nothing to commit; or the user’s message is read-only / questions-only with no file edits.

If multiple workspace roots exist, commit in **each** git repo that had edits.
